stody. Xinhua Vanguard Nigeria News The Ukrainian capital Kiev is set to host the Euro 2012 final, with a number of heads of state and prime ministers expected, despite a political boycott announced by several European countries. July 1, 2012 In "Sports" Italian prosecutors on Friday asked an appeals court to confirm a seven-year prison sentence against former prime minister Silvio Berlusconi for having sex with an underage prostitute and for abuse of power while he was in office. July 11, 2014 In "News" The suspect behind the bombing of a hospital in central Bangkok that left 25 people injured in May was on Wednesday sentenced to 27 years in prison, a court official said. December 6, 2017 In "News"